<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Minimum Menu Height != Number of search results]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7841&amp;p=33789#p33789"><![CDATA[
Don't overthink it <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /> It is what it is, the menu height. Consider the value as just a number which increases the height. The search results that fit in it *will vary* depending on the small/large icon size, and how many search providers you have added. On my PC, the minimum menu height is 20 but I have 8 search providers defined and icon size of 40 so it can show only 6 search results excluding the category headers.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Mon Aug 21, 2017 10:14 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
