<title type="html"><![CDATA[Minimum Menu Height != Number of search results]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7841&amp;p=33787#p33787"><![CDATA[
Good day.<br /><br />Ever since the &quot;Minimum Menu Height&quot; setting was added to Classic Start Menu I have been having a hard time understanding it.<br />The help bubble says it is the minimum number of search results to show.<br /><br />I recently cleared my UserAssist, so now &quot;Minimum Menu Height&quot; is again relevant until I run 15 programs from the Start Menu. I set my Minimum at 18, which should roughly make my menu the same height as when I have 15 Frequent Programs and 3 pinned programs. Anyway, with Minimum=18 I do a search, and the result is NOT 18 results, it is more like 15 results if we include the category headers, and 16 if we include the extra &quot;search for more&quot; at the bottom. Neither of which is 18. I could increase the Minimum value until I do see 18 results, but that is not the point; the point is: I do not understand this value; it does not seem to be the minimum number of search results :-(<br /><br />Screenshots:<br /><a href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/xqgp5i1q0txtb32/CSM-18Min-1.jpg?dl=1" class="postlink">Simple search for TEST</a><br /><a href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/ta4nm2wwykqqb9l/CSM-18Min-2.jpg?dl=1" class="postlink">Search for TEST in a single category</a><br /><br />Thank you.<br />Best Regards,<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=22972">Sylvain</a> — Mon Aug 21, 2017 9:29 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
